---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Recursio"
  description="Terms of Use for the Recursio language-learning app."
  canonicalSlug="terms"
>
  <article class="legal-section">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>

    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p>Using Recursio means the user agrees to these Terms.</p>

    <h2>2. About Recursio</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio provides vocabulary, grammar, recall, writing, and AI-assisted language-learning
      tools.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Accounts</h2>
    <p>
      Users may need to sign in with Apple or Google to save progress, use subscriptions, and sync
      learning data.
    </p>

    <h2>4. User Responsibility</h2>
    <p>
      Users are responsible for the text they submit and must not submit unlawful, harmful,
      abusive, or sensitive personal content.
    </p>

    <h2>5. AI-Assisted Features</h2>
    <p>
      AI features may generate corrections, explanations, practice prompts, and conversation
      responses. AI output may be incomplete or inaccurate. Recursio is not a substitute for a
      human teacher, professional translator, or official language certification.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Subscriptions</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio offers optional paid plans such as SMART and PRO. Subscription terms are described
      on the <a href="/subscription-terms">Subscription Terms</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Acceptable Use</h2>
    <p>Users must not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>misuse the app</li>
      <li>attempt to reverse engineer or disrupt the service</li>
      <li>use the app for illegal purposes</li>
      <li>abuse AI features</li>
      <li>submit content that violates others' rights</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>
      The app, design, text, software, and brand are owned by Recursio or its owner/licensors.
      Users keep responsibility for their own submitted learning content.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Availability and Changes</h2>
    <p>
      Features may change over time. Recursio may add, remove, or modify features, including free
      and paid features.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Termination</h2>
    <p>Access may be limited or terminated if the user violates these Terms.</p>

    <h2>11. Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>Recursio is provided "as is" and does not guarantee specific learning outcomes.</p>

    <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the extent permitted by law, Recursio is not liable for indirect losses, learning
      outcomes, or decisions made based on AI feedback.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</LegalLayout>
